    "answer_id" : 4350118,
    "question_id" : 4350084,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<blockquote>\n  <p>I know it's done with InputStream</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Actually, you'd be <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/io/FileOutputStream.html#write%28byte%5b%5d%29\" rel=\"nofollow\">writing</a> to a <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/io/FileOutputStream.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">file output</a>...</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 246313,
      "reputation" : 10379,
      "user_id" : 520394,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/4af92e99c70b1050b5b7140e9b413c99?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "barti_ddu",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/520394/barti-ddu"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1291413132,
    "creation_date" : 1291413132,
    "answer_id" : 4350182,
    "question_id" : 4350084,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>Basic example:</p>\n\n<pre><code>String fileName = \"file.test\";\n\nBufferedOutputStream bs = null;\n\ntry {\n\n    FileOutputStream fs = new FileOutputStream(new File(fileName));\n    bs = new BufferedOutputStream(fs);\n    bs.write(byte_array);\n    bs.close();\n    bs = null;\n\n} catch (Exception e) {\n    e.printStackTrace()\n}\n\nif (bs != null) try { bs.close(); } catch (Exception e) {}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
