    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>From <strong>Java 7</strong> onward you can use the <em>try-with-resources</em> statement to avoid leaking resources and make your code easier to read. More on that <a href=\"http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/articles/java/trywithresources-401775.html\">here</a>.</p>\n\n<p>To write your <code>byteArray</code> to a file you would do:</p>\n\n<pre><code>try (FileOutputStream fos = new FileOutputStream(\"fullPathToFile\")) {\n    fos.write(byteArray);\n} catch (IOException ioe) {\n    ioe.printStackTrace();\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
